         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ As to the International Exhibition; I have not even seen it &amp; I doubt if I shall. I have no time whatever now to attend to these matters. I believe it will be annual but I think the public interest...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">73.00.00c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS is embossed with the crest of 'Royal Gardens Kew'. The fragment is undated, but the references to John Booth's <name key="Cycas">Cycas</name> and the tree ferns clearly follow on from mentions of them in J. Hooker to M, 15 January 1873. The account of the <name key="Cycas">Cycas</name> seems, however, to report a later stage in their development, suggesting that it was sent later than that letter. The page begins without any salutation.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As to the International Exhibition; I have not even seen it &amp; I doubt if I shall. I have no time whatever now to attend to these matters. I believe it will be annual but I think the public interest in these Exhibitions is fast waning.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">London International Exhibition, 1873. International exhibitions were held annually in London, 1871-4.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Booth has not sent for his <name key="Cycas">Cycas</name> yet, one of the two is growing I hope, at least it is swelling at the top. The other shows no signs of life yet. The 12 ft. tree fern (<name key="Dicksonia">Dicksonia</name>) is doing well, but the 20 ft <name key="Alsophilla">Alsophilla</name> I despair of. The <name key="Todea">Todea</name> is in superb order. <name key="Xanthorrhoea%20quadrangulata">Xanthorrhoea quadrangulata</name> is flowering.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The little box of K.G. Sound<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">King George Sound, WA.</p>
               </note> plants arrived last week, all dead. That Calico plan of roofing does not answer for any thing I find.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We are very busy now with the Flora of British India<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">J. Hooker (1875-97).</p>
               </note> of which I hope to send you Pt II in a month at the outside. Bentham is at <name key="Mimoseae">Mimoseae</name> for Martius Flora<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The final part of Bentham (1859-76), 'Leguminosae, III: <name key="Mimoseae">Mimoseae</name>', was published on 1 July 1876 as vol. 15, part 2, pp. 257-504.</p>
               </note> after which he will proceed to the concluding volume of the Flora Australiensis.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham (1863-78), vol. 7.</p>
               </note> He is remarkably well &amp; very busy with the change of apartments of the Linn. Soc.; which will have him splendidly housed at Burlington House.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The Linnean Society occupied its new rooms in Burlington House, London, at the end of October 1873.</p>
               </note> How I wish that we could welcome you there — but I suppose that you have no intention of taking a holiday &amp; visiting England.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">but …holiday <seg style="font-style: italic; ">is marked with a pencilled line in the margin.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Boronia%20megastigma">Boronia megastigma</name> is flourishing, so our Australia shelves will [bear] a lasting testimony to your services to Scientific Horticulture.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">shelves … Horticulture <seg style="font-style: italic; ">is marked with a pencilled line in the margin.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever my dear Mueller</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Most sincerely your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jos. D Hooker.</p>
